history.content: If you are interested in semiconductors, EE130 is a pset class with a fairly light project at the end. I've also heard it pairs well with EE105, since it will make the device physics portion of 105 a breeze.

children.subject: Could I do this with 123? Seems like it would be a lot of work since 123 is notoriously heavy.

I mean... I personally took 105, 130, and 70 together (with an additional humanities class) and had just enough bandwidth to do well in all of them, so take that as you will. 105 had a notoriously hard semester with Prof. Niknejad, so there's that too. But yeah, the 105 + 130 combo helps significantly, so if you're disciplined it should be possible. Best of luck!
also imo 130 is basically as light as it gets, so no other classes could do better in terms of imposed workload as I see it
+1 130 w/ Prof. Salahuddin is very manageable and makes 105 much easier, 10/10 would recommend.
